{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"TextDecoderStream: fatal property","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/fatal","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.TextDecoderStream.fatal"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Encoding_API\">Encoding API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream\"><code>TextDecoderStream</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/TextDecoderStream\"><code>TextDecoderStream()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/encoding\"><code>encoding</code></a></li><li><em><code>fatal</code> </em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/ignoreBOM\"><code>ignoreBOM</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/readable\"><code>readable</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/writable\"><code>writable</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Encoding API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoder\"><code>TextDecoder</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextEncoder\"><code>TextEncoder</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextEncoderStream\"><code>TextEncoderStream</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>fatal</code></strong> read-only property of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream\"><code>TextDecoderStream</code></a> interface is a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>boolean</code></a> indicating if the error mode of the <code>TextDecoderStream</code> object is set to <code>fatal</code>.</p>\n<p>\n  If the property is <code>true</code> then a decoder will throw a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/TypeError\"><code>TypeError</code></a> if it encounters malformed data while decoding.\n  If <code>false</code> the decoder will substitute the invalid data with the replacement character <code>U+FFFD</code> (ï¿½).\n  The value of the property is set in the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/TextDecoderStream\"><code>TextDecoderStream()</code> constructor</a>.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>boolean</code></a> which will return <code>true</code> if the error mode is set to \"fatal\".\n  Otherwise it returns <code>false</code>, indicating that the error mode is \"replacement\".\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>stream <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">TextDecoderStream</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>stream<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>fatal<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// returns false</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-textdecoder-fatal","title":"Encoding Standard"}],"query":"api.TextDecoderStream.fatal"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.TextDecoderStream.fatal"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The fatal read-only property of the TextDecoderStream interface is a boolean indicating if the error mode of the TextDecoderStream object is set to fatal.","popularity":0,"modified":"2023-04-08T06:16:25.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/textdecoderstream/fatal","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/textdecoderstream/fatal/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/0c8a320b035cf625c1df67713a94ead2e7f3aec6","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"fatal","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream","title":"TextDecoderStream"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoderStream/fatal","title":"fatal"}],"pageTitle":"TextDecoderStream: fatal property - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}